posts.name: BB3539
posts.cooked: If nothing else; with the versplanetary, the shaft should be tapped for 1/4-20.  You can take another shaft and tap that 1/4-20, screw a 1"  bolt into the VP shaft and cut off the head to make a double sided bolt, allowing you to screw the other shaft onto it.  Put a nut on the bolt before you cut the head off so you can reform the threads.
Versa also has a female hex output adapter but its kinda sketchy and you have to space the gearbox away depending on the application

posts.name: Ben Edwards
posts.cooked: Would recommend not using the VP female hex adapter, it is susceptible to shock loads and we broke one a few years ago. Can you use a standard hex output versaplanetary turning gears, chain, or a MAX 90 Degree gearbox? Another consideration is to use a long hex coupler ( QTY 2 - Half Inch Hex Coupler ) and link the versa hex output shaft with the shaft length you need.  That’s far stronger than the female hex ouptut adapter, probably not as good as a MAX 90 degree. I’d sell you a base kit if I had one to sell, we’ve had multiple teams asking about them. Good luck!
We barely use versa planetary stuff anymore. I was just stating that it did exist but is a pain
